.TH ONEBAND "6D" "May 5, 2004" "IRIX 6.5
.SH NAME
oneband - get a single band of an image
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoneband\fP \fBinimage.rgb\fP \fBoutimage.bw\fP \fBband\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fIoneband\fP extracts a single band of a color image. Normally band should be
a number in the range [0...3]. Band 0 is the red part of and RGB image,
while band 1 and 2 are the green and blue bands. Band 3 potentially
represents alpha.
.SH SEE ALSO
cglue(6D)
